cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.PL

The paper combines mathematical programming and machine learning to optimize transprecision computing, which involves reducing precision for improved energy efficiency. This topic falls under the category of computer systems and architecture (cs.AR), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of mixed-precision arithmetic also suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY), while the optimization aspect relates to programming languages (cs.PL).
